# colcon — do not scan packages below this directory.
#
# automaticaddison/mycobot_ros2 (vendored at ./mycobot_ros2/) hardcodes
# ~/ros2_ws/src/mycobot_ros2/ in several launch files (see
# mycobot_description/launch/robot_state_publisher.launch.py). To satisfy
# that assumption you must create a symlink:
#
#   ln -sfT \
#     ~/ros2_ws/src/place-items-on-shelf/robots/mycobot-280-pi/src/mycobot_ros2 \
#     ~/ros2_ws/src/mycobot_ros2
#
# With both this path AND the symlink visible to colcon, scanning would
# double-discover every package. This COLCON_IGNORE file makes colcon
# skip THIS path. The symlinked path at ~/ros2_ws/src/mycobot_ros2 is
# the one colcon sees and builds against.
